{
  "doc_id": "33975",
  "text": "DNA methylation is responsible for transcriptional silencing of Oct4 gene expression [CITATION_1] to induce multi-lineage differentiation of embryo [CITATION_2] . At the same time, DNA methylation of exon 1 is much more linked to transcriptional silencing than the upstream promoter region [CITATION_3] . Therefore, it is meaningful to study the influence of methylation patterns of Oct4 exon 1 to embryonic development. In this study, we firstly focused on one available CpG island methylation region located in exon 1 of bovine Oct4 gene, rather than the methylation status of Oct4 promoter region which was most detected in available publications [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
